Yup.  I use a pot of very hot water, and set the container of gear oil in
it for about 10 minutes before trying to pump it.

Harry Houck wrote:
> Another tip on the gear oil. Heat it up (safely) before pumping. Moves a lot easier and lets air pockets out of the gear boxes faster. The stay-in tip works very well, I did an oil change on the '66 yesterday. 
